  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "hero",
      "headline": "Hiking Up<br/>To 14,505<br/>With My Kids",
      "headlineStyle": {
        "size": "76",
        "weight": "bold",
        "color": "#f5a824",
        "font": "system-ui",
        "style": "normal"
      },
      "deck": "We expected a long trek to the top of Mount Whitney.<br/>What we got was a grueling footslog that pushed us to the limits.",
      "deckStyle": {
        "size": "20",
        "weight": "normal",
        "color": "#ffffff",
        "font": "system-ui",
        "style": "normal"
      },
      "image": "projects/mt_whitney_demo/media/10_above_clouds.jpeg",
      "mobileImage": "projects/mt_whitney_demo/media/11_Whitney_Griffin_hiking.jpeg",
      "video": "",
      "poster": "",
      "focusX": 0.5,
      "focusY": 0.5,
      "overlayOpacity": 0,
      "textPosition": "bottom-left",
      "offsetX": 0,
      "offsetY": 0
    },
    {
      "type": "photo-lede-side",
      "bgColor": "#000000",
      "image": "projects/mt_whitney_demo/media/06_stars.JPG",
      "video": "",
      "poster": "",
      "mobileVideo": "",
      "mobilePoster": "",
      "focusX": 0.5,
      "focusY": 0.5,
      "imageWidth": "50",
      "textWidth": "max-w-lg",
      "textPadding": {
        "top": 16,
        "bottom": 16
      },
      "imagePosition": "right",
      "byline": {
        "text": "By Marcus Chan",
        "style": {
          "size": "20",
          "weight": "normal",
          "color": "#cbd0d7",
          "font": "IBM Plex Sans, sans-serif",
          "style": "normal"
        }
      },
      "location": "Lone Pine, Calif.",
      "date": "Sept. 20, 2025",
      "readTime": "5 min read",
      "subhead": "",
      "subheadStyle": {
        "size": "28",
        "weight": "normal",
        "color": "#f28926",
        "font": "Newsreader, serif",
        "style": "normal"
      },
      "body": [
        {
          "text": "When we woke up in the wee hours of our big day, we saw something we hadn't seen since we arrived: clear skies.",
          "style": {
            "size": "19",
            "weight": "normal",
            "color": "#e5e5e5",
            "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
            "style": "normal",
            "leading": "1.7"
          }
        },
        {
          "text": "For days it had been wet weather around Mount Whitney. It was so bad that just the day before, hikers were forced to turn around near the summit because of blizzard conditions. It's not what you want to hear right before your own attempt.",
          "style": {
            "size": "19",
            "weight": "normal",
            "color": "#e5e5e5",
            "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
            "style": "normal",
            "leading": "1.7"
          }
        },
        {
          "text": "This was an important hike to us. My daughter is named after the mountain, and we'd always hoped to reach the summit together. We trained for months, subjecting ourselves to long hikes on ankle-twisting terrain with heavy packs. But we knew Mother Nature would have the final say.",
          "style": {
            "size": "19",
            "weight": "normal",
            "color": "#e5e5e5",
            "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
            "style": "normal",
            "leading": "1.7"
          }
        },
        {
          "text": "So to wake up to this view was promising. Energized, my daughter, son Griffin and I began our ascent to 14,505.",
          "style": {
            "size": "19",
            "weight": "normal",
            "color": "#e5e5e5",
            "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
            "style": "normal",
            "leading": "1.7"
          }
        }
      ],
      "dropCap": {
        "enabled": true,
        "size": "76",
        "lineHeight": "64",
        "color": "#fbbf24",
        "firstLineSize": "24",
        "firstLineColor": "#ffffff"
      },
      "dividerTop": false,
      "dividerBottom": false,
      "dividerColor": "#4d3d14"
    },
    {
      "type": "photo-lede-side",
      "bgColor": "#000000",
      "image": "",
      "video": "projects/mt_whitney_demo/media/03_Whitney_creek.mp4",
      "poster": "",
      "mobileVideo": "projects/mt_whitney_demo/media/03_Whitney_creek.mp4",
      "mobilePoster": "",
      "focusX": 0.5,
      "focusY": 0.5,
      "imageWidth": "50",
      "textWidth": "max-w-lg",
      "textPadding": {
        "top": 16,
        "bottom": 16
      },
      "imagePosition": "left",
      "byline": {
        "text": "",
        "style": {
          "size": "20",
          "weight": "normal",
          "color": "#cbd0d7",
          "font": "IBM Plex Sans, sans-serif",
          "style": "normal"
        }
      },
      "location": "",
      "date": "",
      "readTime": "",
      "subhead": "2:32 a.m. (half an hour hiking)",
      "subheadStyle": {
        "size": "28",
        "weight": "normal",
        "color": "#f28926",
        "font": "Newsreader, serif",
        "style": "normal"
      },
      "body": [
        {
          "text": "There's nothing technically difficult about the main trail when it's free of snow and ice. Still, you have to watch your step on the rocky path, especially at night.",
          "style": {
            "size": "19",
            "weight": "normal",
            "color": "#e5e5e5",
            "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
            "style": "normal",
            "leading": "1.7"
          }
        },
        {
          "text": "There's little risk of falling off a cliff during the early parts of the hike. But when you climb above 12,000, the drop-offs become steep, the trail can become slippery and you're much more vulnerable to the elements.",
          "style": {
            "size": "19",
            "weight": "normal",
            "color": "#e5e5e5",
            "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
            "style": "normal",
            "leading": "1.7"
          }
        },
        {
          "text": "(Recently, a hiker <a href=\"https://www.sfgate.com/bayarea/article/california-teen-hiker-coma-mount-whitney-20392404.php\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">stepped off a cliff</a> and suffered brain injury. <a href=\"https://www.yahoo.com/news/articles/hiker-killed-slipping-falling-down-172309047.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Another fell</a> to his death amid severe weather conditions. And another hiker just died, possibly while <a href=\"https://www.yahoo.com/news/articles/mt-whitney-rescue-team-finds-020254123.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">taking a shortcut</a> on the long trail.)",
          "style": {
            "size": "19",
            "weight": "normal",
            "color": "#e5e5e5",
            "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
            "style": "normal",
            "leading": "1.7"
          }
        },
        {
          "text": "We're early in our hike, up only 8,800 feet.",
          "style": {
            "size": "19",
            "weight": "normal",
            "color": "#e5e5e5",
            "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
            "style": "normal",
            "leading": "1.7"
          }
        },
        {
          "text": "(To hear the rushing water, unmute in the lower left corner.)",
          "style": {
            "size": "19",
            "weight": "normal",
            "color": "#e5e5e5",
            "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
            "style": "normal",
            "leading": "1.7"
          }
        }
      ],
      "dropCap": {
        "enabled": true,
        "size": "56",
        "lineHeight": "47",
        "color": "#fbbf24",
        "firstLineSize": "22",
        "firstLineColor": "#ffffff"
      },
      "dividerTop": true,
      "dividerBottom": true,
      "dividerColor": "#4d3d14"
    },
    {
      "type": "split-panel",
      "bgColor": "#000000",
      "reversed": true,
      "panels": [
        {
          "image": "projects/mt_whitney_demo/media/09_first_sight.jpeg",
          "video": "",
          "poster": "",
          "focusX": 0.5,
          "focusY": 0.5,
          "subhead": "6:04 a.m. (4 hours hiking)",
          "subheadStyle": {
            "size": "28",
            "weight": "normal",
            "color": "#f28926",
            "font": "Newsreader, serif",
            "style": "normal",
            "align": "left"
          },
          "body": [
            {
              "text": "Daylight comes. After hiking for hours by headlamp, the rising sun reveals the hard, jagged landscape we've been traversing. I feel like I've been transported. We're close to 11,000 feet.",
              "style": {
                "size": "19",
                "weight": "normal",
                "color": "#e5e5e5",
                "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
                "style": "normal",
                "leading": "1.7"
              }
            },
            {
              "text": "We've been moving at a steady pace, but I know Griffin wants to hike faster (because he can). For the sake of the rest of us, he'll have to cool his heels.",
              "style": {
                "size": "19",
                "weight": "normal",
                "color": "#e5e5e5",
                "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
                "style": "normal",
                "leading": "1.7"
              }
            }
          ],
          "body2": [
            {
              "text": "Far off in the distance (upper left corner of the photo), we catch our first glimpse of the famous golden hue (or \"alpenglow\") of the main Mount Whitney massif. That's about 13,000 feet.",
              "style": {
                "size": "19",
                "weight": "normal",
                "color": "#e5e5e5",
                "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
                "style": "normal",
                "leading": "1.7"
              }
            },
            {
              "text": "It's where we're headed.",
              "style": {
                "size": "19",
                "weight": "normal",
                "color": "#e5e5e5",
                "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
                "style": "normal",
                "leading": "1.7"
              }
            }
          ],
          "textWidth": "max-w-lg",
          "textPadding": {
            "top": 16,
            "bottom": 16
          },
          "dropCap": {
            "enabled": true,
            "size": "56",
            "lineHeight": "47",
            "color": "#fbbf24",
            "firstLineSize": "22",
            "firstLineColor": "#ffffff"
          },
          "mobileSubhead": false
        },
        {
          "image": "projects/mt_whitney_demo/media/11_Whitney_Griffin_hiking.jpeg",
          "video": "",
          "poster": "",
          "focusX": 0.5,
          "focusY": 0.5,
          "subhead": "7:26 a.m. (5-1/2 hours hiking)",
          "subheadStyle": {
            "size": "28",
            "weight": "normal",
            "color": "#f28926",
            "font": "Newsreader, serif",
            "style": "normal",
            "align": "left"
          },
          "body": [
            {
              "text": "The clear skies didn't last for long. A sea of clouds slowly creeps up behind us. We're at an elevation of around 11,700 feet.",
              "style": {
                "size": "19",
                "weight": "normal",
                "color": "#e5e5e5",
                "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
                "style": "normal",
                "leading": "1.7"
              }
            },
            {
              "text": "The sun is out, yet it feels colder. The altitude is making us breathe harder.",
              "style": {
                "size": "19",
                "weight": "normal",
                "color": "#e5e5e5",
                "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
                "style": "normal",
                "leading": "1.7"
              }
            }
          ],
          "body2": [
            {
              "text": "We run into only one other person on this leg of the trail. It's a tall, young guy who passes us, but then takes a wrong turn, and ends up behind us.",
              "style": {
                "size": "19",
                "weight": "normal",
                "color": "#e5e5e5",
                "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
                "style": "normal",
                "leading": "1.7"
              }
            },
            {
              "text": "Even though this is a well-worn path, it's not always obvious which way to go. That's why we have GPS-enabled maps on our phones (I'm using FarOut).",
              "style": {
                "size": "19",
                "weight": "normal",
                "color": "#e5e5e5",
                "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
                "style": "normal",
                "leading": "1.7"
              }
            }
          ],
          "textWidth": "max-w-lg",
          "textPadding": {
            "top": 16,
            "bottom": 16
          },
          "dropCap": {
            "enabled": true,
            "size": "56",
            "lineHeight": "47",
            "color": "#fbbf24",
            "firstLineSize": "22",
            "firstLineColor": "#ffffff"
          },
          "mobileSubhead": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "full-bleed",
      "bgColor": "#000000",
      "image": "projects/mt_whitney_demo/media/12_near_Trail_Camp.jpeg",
      "video": "",
      "poster": "",
      "mobileVideo": "",
      "mobilePoster": "",
      "focusX": 0.5,
      "focusY": 0.5,
      "caption": "",
      "captionStyle": {
        "size": "14",
        "weight": "normal",
        "color": "#9ca3af",
        "font": "system-ui",
        "style": "normal"
      },
      "paddingTop": 0,
      "paddingBottom": 0
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "bgColor": "#000000",
      "textWidth": "max-w-4xl",
      "textPadding": {
        "top": 16,
        "bottom": 16
      },
      "subhead": "8:37 a.m. (6-1/2 hours hiking)",
      "subheadStyle": {
        "size": "28",
        "weight": "normal",
        "color": "#f28926",
        "font": "Newsreader, serif",
        "style": "normal"
      },
      "body": [
        {
          "text": "We make it to Trail Camp, which is above 12,000 feet. We started our hike at just under 8,400 feet.",
          "style": {
            "size": "19",
            "weight": "normal",
            "color": "#e5e5e5",
            "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
            "style": "normal",
            "leading": "1.7"
          }
        },
        {
          "text": "At this elevation, the Cleveland Clinic says you shouldn't ascend more than 1,640 feet per day. We've already doubled that amount. To reach the summit, we'll more than triple the recommended daily limit.",
          "style": {
            "size": "19",
            "weight": "normal",
            "color": "#e5e5e5",
            "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
            "style": "normal",
            "leading": "1.7"
          }
        },
        {
          "text": "We're 6 miles in with 5 more hard miles to go to reach the top, starting with a section known as the \"99 switchbacks.\" It's more than 2 miles long and ascends around 1,800 feet. It can become dangerous when there's snow or ice (it's where the two recent fatalities occurred). We packed micro-spikes just in case.",
          "style": {
            "size": "19",
            "weight": "normal",
            "color": "#e5e5e5",
            "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
            "style": "normal",
            "leading": "1.7"
          }
        },
        {
          "text": "We take a short breather by a small lake and gird ourselves for what's to come.",
          "style": {
            "size": "19",
            "weight": "normal",
            "color": "#e5e5e5",
            "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
            "style": "normal",
            "leading": "1.7"
          }
        }
      ],
      "dropCap": {
        "enabled": true,
        "size": "56",
        "lineHeight": "47",
        "color": "#fbbf24",
        "firstLineSize": "22",
        "firstLineColor": "#ffffff"
      }
    },
