    {
      "type": "split-panel",
      "bgColor": "#000000",
      "reversed": false,
      "panels": [
        {
          "image": "",
          "video": "projects/mt_whitney_demo/media/17_Trail_Crest.mp4",
          "poster": "",
          "focusX": 0.5,
          "focusY": 0.5,
          "subhead": "12:45 p.m. (almost 11 hours hiking)",
          "subheadStyle": {
            "size": "28",
            "weight": "normal",
            "color": "#f28926",
            "font": "Newsreader, serif",
            "style": "normal",
            "align": "left"
          },
          "body": [
            {
              "text": "We reach Trail Crest at 13,654 feet. It's significant on several fronts.",
              "style": {
                "size": "19",
                "weight": "normal",
                "color": "#e5e5e5",
                "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
                "style": "normal",
                "leading": "1.7"
              }
            },
            {
              "text": "First, it marks the end of the 99 switchbacks and the start of the toughest leg: 2.8 miles to the summit.",
              "style": {
                "size": "19",
                "weight": "normal",
                "color": "#e5e5e5",
                "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
                "style": "normal",
                "leading": "1.7"
              }
            },
            {
              "text": "Second, this is where blizzard conditions the day before forced hikers to abandon their summit bid. As you can see, there's little protection from storms or strong winds along the narrow ridge.",
              "style": {
                "size": "19",
                "weight": "normal",
                "color": "#e5e5e5",
                "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
                "style": "normal",
                "leading": "1.7"
              }
            },
            {
              "text": "And third, this is roughly where Whitney and I turned back last year during our first attempt together. On that occasion, the altitude made Whitney feel ill. She was determined to push on, but I didn't think it was safe, so we descended.",
              "style": {
                "size": "19",
                "weight": "normal",
                "color": "#e5e5e5",
                "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
                "style": "normal",
                "leading": "1.7"
              }
            },
            {
              "text": "She felt much better today.",
              "style": {
                "size": "19",
                "weight": "normal",
                "color": "#e5e5e5",
                "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
                "style": "normal",
                "leading": "1.7"
              }
            }
          ],
          "body2": [],
          "textWidth": "max-w-lg",
          "textPadding": {
            "top": 16,
            "bottom": 16
          },
          "dropCap": {
            "enabled": true,
            "size": "56",
            "lineHeight": "47",
            "color": "#fbbf24",
            "firstLineSize": "22",
            "firstLineColor": "#ffffff"
          },
          "mobileSubhead": false
        },
        {
          "image": "",
          "video": "projects/mt_whitney_demo/media/19_Trail_Crest_cliff.mp4",
          "poster": "",
          "focusX": 0.5,
          "focusY": 0.5,
          "subhead": "Don't Look Down",
          "subheadStyle": {
            "size": "28",
            "weight": "normal",
            "color": "#f28926",
            "font": "Newsreader, serif",
            "style": "normal",
            "align": "left"
          },
          "body": [
            {
              "text": "Remember when I said it gets a bit more risky above 12,000 feet? This is what I meant.",
              "style": {
                "size": "19",
                "weight": "normal",
                "color": "#e5e5e5",
                "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
                "style": "normal",
                "leading": "1.7"
              }
            },
            {
              "text": "The video was taken about 4 feet from the middle of the trail. There are many steep drop-offs like this along the last leg.",
              "style": {
                "size": "19",
                "weight": "normal",
                "color": "#e5e5e5",
                "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
                "style": "normal",
                "leading": "1.7"
              }
            },
            {
              "text": "On top of that, if you see dark clouds coming, this sign below becomes more important. That hissing (bullet #3) may not be a snake.",
              "style": {
                "size": "19",
                "weight": "normal",
                "color": "#e5e5e5",
                "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
                "style": "normal",
                "leading": "1.7"
              }
            }
          ],
          "body2": [],
          "inlineImage": "projects/mt_whitney_demo/media/20_danger_sign.jpeg",
          "inlineImageWidth": "max-w-sm",
          "textWidth": "max-w-lg",
          "textPadding": {
            "top": 16,
            "bottom": 16
          },
          "dropCap": {
            "enabled": true,
            "size": "56",
            "lineHeight": "47",
            "color": "#fbbf24",
            "firstLineSize": "22",
            "firstLineColor": "#ffffff"
          },
          "mobileSubhead": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "split-panel",
      "bgColor": "#000000",
      "reversed": false,
      "panels": [
        {
          "image": "",
          "video": "projects/mt_whitney_demo/media/22_slow_steps.mp4",
          "poster": "",
          "focusX": 0.5,
          "focusY": 0.5,
          "subhead": "Higher and Slower",
          "subheadStyle": {
            "size": "28",
            "weight": "normal",
            "color": "#f28926",
            "font": "Newsreader, serif",
            "style": "normal",
            "align": "left"
          },
          "body": [
            {
              "text": "For those who have never felt the enfeebling effects of high altitudes, hiking another 2.8 miles can feel insurmountable.",
              "style": {
                "size": "19",
                "weight": "normal",
                "color": "#e5e5e5",
                "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
                "style": "normal",
                "leading": "1.7"
              }
            },
            {
              "text": "Each step takes effort and the breathing only gets harder as you climb above 13,500 feet.",
              "style": {
                "size": "19",
                "weight": "normal",
                "color": "#e5e5e5",
                "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
                "style": "normal",
                "leading": "1.7"
              }
            }
          ],
          "body2": [
            {
              "text": "Meanwhile, your brain tells you that you've gone too far to turn back, just as your body insists you still have much too far to go.",
              "style": {
                "size": "19",
                "weight": "normal",
                "color": "#e5e5e5",
                "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
                "style": "normal",
                "leading": "1.7"
              }
            },
            {
              "text": "There's a delicate balance of pushing forward but not endangering yourself or the group.",
              "style": {
                "size": "19",
                "weight": "normal",
                "color": "#e5e5e5",
                "font": "Inter, sans-serif",
                "style": "normal",
                "leading": "1.7"
              }
            }
          ],
          "textWidth": "max-w-lg",
          "textPadding": {
